org.processmining.hybridilpminer.models.lp.variablemapping.interfaces

Interface HybridVariableMapping<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - refers to the type of the "letters" / "events" used within the language / log on top of which we build an ILP.
    All Superinterfaces:
    VariableMapping
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SlackBasedFilterHybridVariableMapping<T,S>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HybridVariableMappingImpl, IntArrSlackBasedFilterHybridVariableMapping, SlackBasedFilterHybridVariableMappingImpl

    public interface HybridVariableMapping<T>
extends VariableMapping
    A hybrid variable mapping, maps some object to an LP index, according to the definition of hybrid regions. From a definition point of view the generic type parameter T refers to the type of the "letters" / "events" used within the language / log on top of which we build an ILP.
    Author:
    svzelst
